SIMPLE: isopoda
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isopoda
<hw>I*sop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Iso-</er>, and <er>-poda</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
order of sessile-eyed Crustacea, usually having seven pairs of legs,
which are all similar in structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The body is usually depressed, with the abdominal
segments short, and often consolidated in part. The branchi⟦ae⟧ are on
the abdominal appendages. The group includes the terrestrial pill bugs
and sow bugs, with numerous marine forms. See <er>Arthrostrata</er>,
<er>Gribble</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isopodiform</ent>⟦br⟧
